He did, didn't he?
It's okay if he has.

79
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:18,077
What did he say?

80
00:06:18,812 --> 00:06:20,179
I'm loving this.

81
00:06:20,181 --> 00:06:21,614
Oh, thank you.

82
00:06:21,616 --> 00:06:24,683
I couldn't pull it off.
My hair seems to hate me.

83
00:06:24,685 --> 00:06:26,852
That's where you're supposed to say,
"Your hair's lovely. "

84
00:06:26,854 --> 00:06:28,687
Oh, it, is.
It is lovely.

85
00:06:28,689 --> 00:06:30,255
Okay.

86
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:31,457
I like her.

87
00:06:31,459 --> 00:06:32,992
What's not to like?

88
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:38,697
Get it where you can. I'd be on
my back after a line like that.

89
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:44,871
Susanna, Trent's here.

90
00:06:44,873 --> 00:06:46,840
This is his new girlfriend,
Pam.

91
00:06:46,842 --> 00:06:48,408
Hi, Susanna.

92
00:06:49,777 --> 00:06:51,011
Say, "Hi. "

93
00:06:51,846 --> 00:06:53,013
Hi.

94
00:06:54,682 --> 00:06:58,084
Yeah, but don't come down.

95
00:06:58,086 --> 00:07:00,520
Just stand there, brooding.

96
00:07:00,988 --> 00:07:02,389
Oh!

97
00:07:02,391 --> 00:07:04,858
You've brought me a man.
How thoughtful.

98
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:06,760
Hello, sailor.

99
00:07:06,762 --> 00:07:10,664
Who is this in all his
awkward stage glory?

100
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:11,765
This is my son, Duncan.

101
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:13,299
Everybody lends a hand.

102
00:07:13,301 --> 00:07:15,468
Oh, my God. I was going to name
my youngest Duncan,

103
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:17,303
but my ex-husband thought
it was too nerdy.

104
00:07:17,305 --> 00:07:19,739
So, we went with Peter.
Which, personally, I think is worse.

105
00:07:19,741 --> 00:07:21,174
But, it suits my son, so...

106
00:07:21,176 --> 00:07:23,410
Oh, don't worry,
you wear the name well.

107
00:07:23,412 --> 00:07:24,577
Trent, where's Steph?

108
00:07:24,579 --> 00:07:26,312
We've been here
all of two minutes,

109
00:07:26,314 --> 00:07:27,981
so I suppose she's getting ready
for the beach.

110
00:07:27,983 --> 00:07:30,383
Oh, my God. She's just like me.
Screw cancer.

111
00:07:30,385 --> 00:07:32,919
I want to be an even golden brown.
Everywhere.

112
00:07:32,921 --> 00:07:35,588
Everybody's back this year.
The Gales. The Hutchisons.

113
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:37,757
The Campbells, sans Ben
because of the trial.

114
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:39,492
Insider trading.

115
00:07:39,494 --> 00:07:42,429
The Smythes. Oh, and the Keegans,
who I'm not talking to.

116
00:07:42,431 --> 00:07:45,331
You can if you want to,
but just know that most of us aren't.

117
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,566
Okay.

118
00:07:46,568 --> 00:07:48,368
So, do you think you will?
Pam?

119
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:49,669
Do I think I will, what?

120
00:07:49,671 --> 00:07:51,905
Talk to the Keegans.

121
00:07:51,907 --> 00:07:54,207
Oh, I don't know.
I don't even know them.

122
00:07:54,209 --> 00:07:57,077
Do if you want to but just know
that I'm mad at them.

123
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:59,345
I don't even want
to get into why.

124
00:07:59,347 --> 00:08:01,882
They called me a
See-You-Next-Tuesday.

125
00:08:01,884 --> 00:08:03,584
To my face.

126
00:08:03,586 --> 00:08:05,619
You're going to love it here!
Whoo!

127
00:08:05,621 --> 00:08:07,321
I've only had one.

128
00:08:08,256 --> 00:08:09,590
Yee-haw!

129
00:08:14,429 --> 00:08:15,930
So, how was your winter?

130
00:08:15,932 --> 00:08:17,565
Because our year
was a challenge.

131
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:18,899
My niece was raped in October.

132
00:08:20,102 --> 00:08:21,235
Oh, my God!

133
00:08:21,237 --> 00:08:23,237
I know.
Not even food courts are safe

134
00:08:23,239 --> 00:08:25,306
Oh, and Bob, that's my ex-husband.

135
00:08:25,308 --> 00:08:26,974
Finally came out of
the closet. Not a shock.

136
00:08:26,976 --> 00:08:28,275
Let's just say that, in bed,

137
00:08:28,277 --> 00:08:30,811
his favorite view was
the back of my head.

138
00:08:30,813 --> 00:08:33,948
My oldest, Charlie, is still into
the drugs and psychedelic music.

139
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:38,185
Drugs I get. But, come on,
Gary Garcia's dead! Get over it.

140
00:08:38,187 --> 00:08:39,286
Gary?

141
00:08:39,288 --> 00:08:40,387
Don't do drugs, Declan.

142
00:08:40,389 --> 00:08:41,722
Duncan.

143
00:08:41,724 --> 00:08:43,724
Oh, and Susanna. You saw her.
She's a walking mood.

144
00:08:43,726 --> 00:08:45,526
She's going through
an "I hate my mother" phase.

145
00:08:45,528 --> 00:08:46,794
Taking her father's side, as usual.

146
00:08:46,796 --> 00:08:47,895
Hi, Mrs. Thompson.

147
00:08:47,897 --> 00:08:51,232
Oh, Steph, don't you look so cute.

148
00:08:51,234 --> 00:08:52,566
That's exactly
the kind of suit that

149
00:08:52,568 --> 00:08:53,868
got me pregnant the first time.

150
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:55,269
That's what I'm hoping for.

151
00:08:55,271 --> 00:08:56,370
Hey.

152
00:08:56,372 --> 00:08:58,339
I'm kidding!

153
00:08:58,341 --> 00:09:00,574
Oh, and Peter. Finally got his surgery
to fix his lazy eye.

154
00:09:00,576 --> 00:09:01,842
Now, it's even worse.

155
00:09:01,844 --> 00:09:03,344
I try to get him to
wear an eye patch,

156
00:09:03,346 --> 00:09:06,881
so people don't feel awkward.
But, what are you gonna do?

157
00:09:06,883 --> 00:09:08,015
I'm outta here.

158
00:09:08,017 --> 00:09:10,317
Oh, why don't you
take Duncan with you?

159
00:09:10,319 --> 00:09:14,088
Screw that. I told you I'm not
baby-sitting him all summer.

160
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:16,090
You're gonna take Duncan with you,
young lady. All right?

161
00:09:16,092 --> 00:09:17,758
Why don't you go to the beach, honey?
You'll have fun.

162
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,795
We're just going to
be unpacking here.

163
00:09:19,797 --> 00:09:22,230
We might be doing
some other stuff, too.

164
00:09:22,632 --> 00:09:24,099
Mmm.

165
00:09:26,103 --> 00:09:28,103
That's our cue, kids.
Come on.

166
00:09:28,105 --> 00:09:30,572
Now, listen, I am still having my
annual Fourth of July Clambake.

167
00:09:30,574 --> 00:09:31,673
And it will bleed into your yard.

168
00:09:31,675 --> 00:09:32,774
Okay.

169
00:09:32,776 --> 00:09:35,110
Bob or no Bob,
the party must go on.

170
00:09:35,112 --> 00:09:37,078
He's probably sliding
off our gardener right now.

171
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,814
Let's have a fun summer!

172
00:09:41,852 --> 00:09:43,518
Duncan, are you coming or what?

173
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:55,831
Have fun.

174
00:10:00,837 --> 00:10:02,604
Just keep your distance.

175
00:10:02,606 --> 00:10:06,508
